Definition: a terrorist organization founded by Osama bin Laden in the 1980s to provide money and recruit fighters around the world
Example: enlisted and transported thousands of men to Afghanistan to fight the Russians; a split in the group led bin Laden and the extremist faction of MAK to form al-Qaeda
Synonyms: MAK, terrorist_organization, i, noun, act, terrorism, c, a, terrorist, organization, founded, by, Osama, bin, Laden, in, the, s, to, provide, money, and, recruit, fighters, around, world, enlisted, transported, thousands, of, men, Afghanistan, fight, Russians, split, group, led, extremist, faction, form, al-Qaeda
Category: noun.group
